00:55:51.197 --> 00:55:53.030
Could you help outline
three clearly defined

00:55:53.030 --> 00:55:54.740
simple and effective
steps that one

00:55:54.740 --> 00:55:57.140
can incorporate into their
parenting starting tomorrow?

00:55:57.140 --> 00:55:58.556
RICK HANSON: I
wish more questions

00:55:58.556 --> 00:56:02.360
came to me in this form,
clear, concise, direct.

00:56:02.360 --> 00:56:03.110
It's really great.

00:56:03.110 --> 00:56:05.109
Well, for one, I work
with a lot of kids.

00:56:05.109 --> 00:56:07.400
I have a background there,
and my dissertation actually

00:56:07.400 --> 00:56:08.570
was on 15-month-olds.

00:56:08.570 --> 00:56:11.510
So I have a real interest
in early childhood, too.

00:56:11.510 --> 00:56:13.940
So I think the
question is really apt.

00:56:13.940 --> 00:56:16.200
So three practical suggestions.

00:56:16.200 --> 00:56:18.830
One is up to the
age of around 14,

00:56:18.830 --> 00:56:21.590
when kids no longer will
put up with their parents

00:56:21.590 --> 00:56:25.460
putting them to bed, that
period just before sleep

00:56:25.460 --> 00:56:29.750
is a wonderful opportunity for
a couple, three minutes to rest

00:56:29.750 --> 00:56:33.710
attention on something wholesome
and beneficial for the child,

00:56:33.710 --> 00:56:36.260
which could be as simple
as just feeling cozy

00:56:36.260 --> 00:56:40.160
and cuddly with a caregiver
or happy about the dog that's

00:56:40.160 --> 00:56:42.740
in the room, or talking
about some neat thing that

00:56:42.740 --> 00:56:44.150
happened in the day.

00:56:44.150 --> 00:56:47.030
And then for those few
minutes, just sort of marinate

00:56:47.030 --> 00:56:48.330
in the experience.

00:56:48.330 --> 00:56:50.840
I've known a number of
families in which they started

00:56:50.840 --> 00:56:52.400
doing that with
their kids, and there

00:56:52.400 --> 00:56:54.080
were fairly dramatic benefits.

00:56:54.080 --> 00:56:55.960
Part of it's
implicit, obviously,

00:56:55.960 --> 00:56:58.400
keep sustaining a parent's
attention, let's say.

00:56:58.400 --> 00:57:01.340
But I think in particular,
there is some internalization.

00:57:01.340 --> 00:57:02.390
That's one.

00:57:02.390 --> 00:57:06.830
Two, in formal settings, like
school teachers, educators,

00:57:06.830 --> 00:57:09.050
or mindfulness
coaches, there are so

00:57:09.050 --> 00:57:11.690
many opportunities that
are natural moments

00:57:11.690 --> 00:57:14.720
to slow it down and
help it sink in.

00:57:14.720 --> 00:57:18.050
When kids come back from
recess or after a period

00:57:18.050 --> 00:57:22.220
or before going home, use
those more formal opportunities

00:57:22.220 --> 00:57:25.280
for internalization or
similar opportunities,

00:57:25.280 --> 00:57:27.680
like at meals, in a
family where people just

00:57:27.680 --> 00:57:30.950
take a moment with or without
any religious framework,

00:57:30.950 --> 00:57:32.530
and just be grateful
for the food.

00:57:32.530 --> 00:57:33.530
Just think of something.

00:57:33.530 --> 00:57:35.360
Or just go around
the room, what's

00:57:35.360 --> 00:57:36.977
one good thing that
happened today,

00:57:36.977 --> 00:57:38.810
and it can be the same
good thing every day.

00:57:38.810 --> 00:57:39.620
That's all right.

00:57:39.620 --> 00:57:41.536
But what's one good thing
that happened today.

00:57:41.536 --> 00:57:43.680
People do different things
at formal opportunities.

00:57:43.680 --> 00:57:46.490
And then the last is with this
particular child or really

00:57:46.490 --> 00:57:50.300
any child, ask that question,
what resources would really

00:57:50.300 --> 00:57:53.210
help if they were more present
in the mind of the child,

00:57:53.210 --> 00:57:56.630
and know what is it we're
trying to develop in this child,

00:57:56.630 --> 00:57:59.870
not based on Mom or
Dad's infinite wisdom.

00:57:59.870 --> 00:58:02.900
I speak from some experience
here, some kind of lecture

00:58:02.900 --> 00:58:05.090
coming at the kid,
that they blow off.

00:58:05.090 --> 00:58:07.160
But from the
child's perspective,

00:58:07.160 --> 00:58:08.990
what would the
child be motivated

00:58:08.990 --> 00:58:11.480
to develop more inside
themselves, especially

00:58:11.480 --> 00:58:14.120
social emotional
resources, and then

00:58:14.120 --> 00:58:16.670
if you know what
you're trying to grow,

00:58:16.670 --> 00:58:18.750
which is where the
issue is in most cases,

00:58:18.750 --> 00:58:20.690
people don't know what
they're trying to grow.

00:58:20.690 --> 00:58:22.310
Know what you're trying to grow.

00:58:22.310 --> 00:58:24.740
If you know what you're trying
to develop and encourage

00:58:24.740 --> 00:58:26.660
and nourish and
protect in that child,

00:58:26.660 --> 00:58:29.570
then look for opportunities
to have experiences of that,

00:58:29.570 --> 00:58:33.020
which then are internalized.

